-   Concavity and ConcavePoints (0.9213910)

The problem with collinearity is it makes it difficult to separate out
the individual effects of collinear variables on the dependent variable,
Y. It also reduces accuracy of the estimates of coefficients leading to
higher standard error in coefficient estimates.

To solve this we can drop one of the problematic (highly correlated) X
variables from the model, say Concavity. We can also combine the
collinear variables together into a single predictor such as taking the
average of standardized versions of two correlated variables, say
Compactness and Concavity, to create a new variable)
